cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a novel network structure for enhancing the feature representation capability of CNNs for person re-identification. This involves modeling interdependencies between spatial and channel features and aggregating correlated features. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with image processing and recognition, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of neural networks and feature representation also suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with security and privacy, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
